{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"0429fbfdb6769135","type":"text","text":"**ACTIVITIES**","x":-1243,"y":-30,"width":930,"height":60,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"5f593a6fa24cb497","type":"text","text":"**Outputs**","x":-213,"y":-30,"width":250,"height":60,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"3384e3be968ce48a","type":"text","text":"**Outcomes**","x":137,"y":-30,"width":758,"height":60,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"5120cb545b808668","type":"text","text":"**A more thorough theory change document than this one!**","x":-213,"y":80,"width":250,"height":130},
		{"id":"b6adf6e6f3023fdf","type":"text","text":"**Fundraise.**  The organization leadership will fundraise from grants to be able to cover the program costs.","x":-1241,"y":400,"width":926,"height":80},
		{"id":"bcae54bc3da8225d","type":"text","text":"**Program funding.**","x":-213,"y":400,"width":250,"height":80},
		{"id":"97e16234875b3b13","type":"text","text":"**Create an application and evaluation procedure.** The organization's candidate selection team create a process for candidates to apply and be evaluated. This will likely involve a written application, some skills assessment, a review of their background, and some in-person evaluation.","x":-1243,"y":548,"width":251,"height":425},
		{"id":"63d9459bd7fd53af","type":"text","text":"**Advertise program and selection process.** The organization communications team create and broadcast informational material about the program and the application process. Some strategies to consider are:\n1. Advertising on online student forums.\n2. Advertising in newspapers.\n3. Advertising on radio.\n4. Advertising on social media.\n5. Visiting high schools or high school conferences to present the program and distribute material.\n6. Visiting teacher's union meetings to present the program and distribute material.\n7. Visiting other community gatherings.\n\nThe advertising should be done in a manner that maximizes the reach to students they think will have the highest expected benefit from the program.","x":-920,"y":548,"width":605,"height":425},
		{"id":"f56dd42988c1cc9a","type":"text","text":"**Implement application and evaluation procedure.** The organization's candidate selection team implement the application and evaluation procedure to select candidates they will help apply to German bachelor's education.","x":-1241,"y":1040,"width":926,"height":120},
		{"id":"fbb0ff09f58bd333","type":"text","text":"**Assist selected students with applications to German bachelor's.** The program team will help students understand the application process and prepare their applications. Some key tasks include:\n1. Helping selected students obtain the necessary documentation to apply for the programs (i.e., passports, birth certificates).\n2. Guiding students through the application process (i.e., explaining new concepts, reminding about key deadlines).\n3. Providing training on how to prepare successful applications.\n\t1. This task could potentially be conducted by a consultant.","x":-1241,"y":1215,"width":926,"height":265},
		{"id":"f135d09fea02f019","type":"text","text":"**Student applications to German universities.**","x":-213,"y":1215,"width":250,"height":105},
		{"id":"01f5764857d5e14e","type":"text","text":"**A set of high school students to assist with applications to German universities.**","x":-213,"y":1040,"width":250,"height":120},
		{"id":"254e89677b602e68","type":"text","text":"**Student acceptances at German universities.**","x":-213,"y":1388,"width":250,"height":92},
		{"id":"c62fdbc26d386b0f","type":"text","text":"**Identify travel and accommodation to Germany for selected students.** The program team will assist students in finding accommodation during their university degree and arrange for their travel.\n\nFor accommodation, the program team may look to establish a network of individuals who are willing to host the students, or finding group housing for the students. The former option seems preferable as it would help integrate the students into German society.\n\nFor travel, the team will purchase plane tickets at the appropriate dates, provide transport to and from the airports in Uganda and Germany, and ensure that students have required travel documents (i.e., passport, visa, vaccinations).","x":-1241,"y":1540,"width":926,"height":260},
		{"id":"13392a384b4586c0","type":"text","text":"**Pay for university, travel and accommodation.**  The organization finance team will pay the universities, travel companies, and accommodation for their services.","x":-1241,"y":1840,"width":926,"height":80},
		{"id":"2518546b705ed59b","type":"text","text":"**Provide training on succeeding at German university.**  The organization program team will provide ongoing training on how to succeed at university in Germany. This training will include study strategies, time management, and integration into society. This training may be best suited to be conducted by external consultants.","x":-1241,"y":2000,"width":425,"height":280},
		{"id":"3635877ed1323c38","type":"text","text":"**Provide training on living in Germany.**  The organization program team will provide training on how to navigate German life. This training will include guides on how to navigate German social and legal services, how to find communities of new friends, and cultural differences to be prepared for. This training may be best suited to be conducted by external experts of previous program participants.","x":-740,"y":2000,"width":425,"height":280},
		{"id":"041b69379281693b","type":"text","text":"**Ensure students have materials for succeeding at university.**  The program and finance team will purchase required materials for students to succeed at university, such as laptops, textbooks, and writing materials. ","x":-1028,"y":2400,"width":425,"height":160},
		{"id":"5c7ce9eb393833da","type":"text","text":"**Provide ongoing troubleshooting for students abroad.**  The program team remain in regular contact with students in Germany and help them troubleshoot and discrete problems, such as acute financial need, academic underperformance or trouble navigating social services.","x":-1028,"y":2640,"width":425,"height":180},
		{"id":"4a4c500fe786170f","type":"text","text":"**Students travel to Germany.**","x":-213,"y":2090,"width":250,"height":100},
		{"id":"146f84ead7d2662f","type":"text","text":"**Confirmed accommodation for the students for their duration of stay in Germany.**","x":-213,"y":1710,"width":250,"height":170},
		{"id":"17e5ee073712543e","type":"text","text":"**Plane tickets.**","x":-213,"y":1540,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"86302694b487bf09","type":"text","text":"**Advertising materials.** Such as radio adverts, pamphlets, presentations.","x":-213,"y":548,"width":250,"height":120},
		{"id":"867f139d279caa7c","type":"text","text":"**Awareness of the program among potential candidates.**","x":-213,"y":720,"width":250,"height":120},
		{"id":"a7d8653e5c801020","type":"text","text":"**Applications for the program.**","x":-213,"y":893,"width":250,"height":80},
		{"id":"ba7c6a332ba703d4","type":"text","text":"**Students begin their course of study.**","x":-213,"y":2450,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"9e699ca9986a7f9f","type":"text","text":"**Students graduate with a bachelor's degree from Germany.**","x":-213,"y":2670,"width":250,"height":120},
		{"id":"9b386934a11ba020","type":"text","text":"**Research how to implement program most effectively.** The organization leaders research how to implement the program in a manner that has the highest expected value in terms of increasing income and overall wellbeing. Some key questions they should answer are:\n1. What individuals would benefit most from studying in Germany?\n2. What individuals would be most likely to successfully complete a bachelor's in Germany?\n3. What universities and degrees offer the best opportunities for increasing incomes and maximizing the likelihood of students succeeding?\n4. What degrees hold the most positive spillovers from the work that the candidates may go on to do?\n5. What are some of the most likely pitfalls that students might experience?","x":-1241,"y":70,"width":930,"height":280},
		{"id":"37cbd7a293d9aea0","type":"text","text":"**Students gain valuable professional skills.**","x":137,"y":2693,"width":250,"height":75},
		{"id":"3c1af821000205dc","type":"text","text":"**Some students obtain a high earning job in Germany or another country abroad.**","x":617,"y":2650,"width":278,"height":160},
		{"id":"656fd434e8faab77","type":"text","text":"**Some students seek further education.**","x":631,"y":2410,"width":250,"height":120},
		{"id":"672cf4f15f6cb354","type":"text","text":"**Students obtain a professional network in Germany.** This helps them find a higher earning job and passively improve their skills.","x":137,"y":2290,"width":250,"height":190},
		{"id":"21562e0f2c6228c3","type":"text","text":"**Students arrive in a country with better social and health services.** This improves their quality of life in terms of improved health and wellbeing.","x":137,"y":2040,"width":250,"height":202},
		{"id":"c06ff52b7f05d960","type":"text","text":"**Some students return to Uganda and find employment.** They apply the skills learned abroad, providing higher economic/social value in Uganda.","x":594,"y":2055,"width":287,"height":173},
		{"id":"104e650f32cddf9a","type":"text","text":"**Some students remaining abroad send remittances back to Uganda.**","x":1040,"y":2462,"width":250,"height":124},
		{"id":"1a9a6d03913c537f","type":"text","text":"**Some students help their family more abroad to a higher income country.**","x":1040,"y":2655,"width":250,"height":161},
		{"id":"fd66f273a389720c","type":"text","text":"**Higher wellbeing for the invidual's family.** They can afford more goods and services that improve their quality of life.","x":1480,"y":2542,"width":250,"height":143},
		{"id":"5939ec957ba2eb74","type":"text","text":"**Ugandan society benefits from more highly educated individual.** These benefits could come in the form of higher productivity of the educated individual, or the social benefits of the work they undertake.","x":1040,"y":1710,"width":250,"height":276},
		{"id":"38e321a2c52fb9a7","type":"text","text":"**Higher wellbeing in Ugandan society.** More economic and social value improves quality of life in Uganda.","x":1480,"y":1775,"width":250,"height":146},
		{"id":"6776f8a29d3a5a7a","type":"text","text":"**Impact**","x":1000,"y":-30,"width":730,"height":60,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"a4dbc56be5dd7c26","type":"text","text":"**More job satisfaaction for the individual.** They may prefer the job they can get with their education.","x":1040,"y":2290,"width":250,"height":136},
		{"id":"980d3f895929b054","type":"text","text":"**Higher income for student than with Uganda education.**","x":1040,"y":2090,"width":250,"height":135},
		{"id":"2a8872466a4f25cc","type":"text","text":"**Higher wellbeing for individual.** They can afford more goods and services that improve their quality of life. They may also have higher life satisfaction living abroad (for instance if a part of their identity made living in Uganda challenging, or they find a more satisfying job abroad).","x":1480,"y":2090,"width":250,"height":372}
	],
